1. Came back again for Hor Fun this time. Not so bad but still got room for improvement ( Not piping hot as the sauce just drenched over it w/o cooking together with the Hor Fun, hence the texture not soft  & smooth enough to complement. )

This coffee shop offers some of the finest coffee I've ever tasted. The service is exceptional, with the owner and staff always attentive and proactive in taking orders. Additionally, their Thai cuisine is a must-try, especially the flavorful Tom Yam soup and a variety of other delectable dishes. The roast duck is another highlight, though it's worth noting they close at 2 pm. I've also heard rave reviews about their vegetarian options, and it's clear they have a dedicated fan base, though I have yet to sample them myself.
